</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/31/03 9:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=681.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Roleplay guild for goodies</span><hr size=1> The Order of the Fiery Heart, a good-aligned guild, focuses on roleplaying and hunting in a family environment that is blessedly devoid of the OOC drama and immaturity you encounter in most guilds. We have only on a couple of occasions actively recruited or advertised for recruits; our members are all people guildmates have met in the game, or on boards like this one, and befriended.<br>
<br>
Given our small size (we are merely 20, including our current inactives) and the fact that most of our guildmates are in their 40's and 50's, we may not be what you are looking for (hard to find guildmates to hunt with unless you are seeking what would effectively amount to power-leveling), but if you are interested in roleplaying, feel free to send me, or anyone else wearing our tag, a tell.<br>
<br>
Speaking for myself, consider the same offer extended if you need help with anything; there <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>are</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> times when having a high-level knight on your friend list might prove an advantage. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
